changelog=0.2.5: Manual and scheduled scans now rebuild file state from the current task set, clearing stale pending and failed records from previous tasks, and add a separate Existing metric for files already present in pCloud.<br>0.2.4: Removed the default pCloud root setting from the UI, made each task pCloud folder the exact remote destination, opened the remote picker from root when no folder is selected, and added Stop Sync to abort active uploads back to pending.<br>0.2.3: Added file size and active upload progress to Sync Logs, fixed unrealistic upload speed spikes, and bound the raw app port to host loopback by default so unauthenticated APIs stay behind the fnOS reverse proxy.<br>0.2.2: Added configurable sync log retention by age and count, plus a one-click log delete action. Settings now shows task configuration first, moves less common pCloud authorization and sync rules below it, documents that pCloud official upload docs do not publish a recommended concurrency number, and removes the decorative window dots and sidebar brand text.<br>0.2.1: Bumped the package version for fnOS installation and upgrade detection. Sync logs now focus on file-level upload results, task cards are compact, saved access tokens show a masked value in the UI, and deleting all tasks also clears migrated legacy sources.<br>0.2.0: Added multi-task upload jobs, sidebar navigation, local folder picker, pCloud remote folder picker, remote folder creation, aggregate upload speed, and pCloud API integrations for getapiserver, currentserver, uploadprogress, checksumfile, and diff.<br>0.1.9: Reworked sync logs as a filterable table, added per-file success records, and drained the pending queue after retrying failed or stuck files.<br>0.1.8: Fixed stuck uploading records when no failures were visible, and exposed running version plus uploading file details in the status API and UI.<br>0.1.7: Added rsync-like remote comparison so unchanged cloud files are skipped while missing or changed files are uploaded, and cleaned up old dashed state.<br>0.1.6: Recovered interrupted uploads that stayed in uploading state, and migrated old dashed remote directory names to normalized directories.<br>0.1.5: Preserved non-ASCII source folder names instead of converting them to dashed remote folders, with migration for old dashed configuration.<br>0.1.4: Created remote directories parent-first, serialized state saves, and added Content-Length plus transient socket retry handling for uploads.<br>0.1.3: Fixed pCloud OAuth access token API calls to use access_token.<br>0.1.2: Switched the default base image to an explicit mirror-friendly Node image.<br>0.1.1: Made the Node base image configurable to avoid public registry pull failures.<br>0.1.0: Initial one-way upload sync with pCloud OAuth, folder configuration, status counters, and failed-file retry.
